%N A097618 Successive basic U.S. postal rates since "uniform" rates (based on weight, not distance) were adopted in 1863.
%C A097618 Complete through July 13, 2025. - _Harvey P. Dale_, Jul 06 2026
%H A097618 <a href="http://about.usps.com/who-we-are/postal-history/domestic-letter-rates-since-1863.htm">History of U.S. Postal Service</a>
%e A097618 The basic domestic letter rate was 3 cents from 1863 to 1883, then 2 cents until 1917, then 3 cents until 1919 when it dropped to 2 cents for the last time.
